imageWriter:Image Writer|Specifies Java Image IO Image Writer and Write Parameter used for compressing DICOM images
imageWriter.dicomTransferSyntax:Transfer Syntax|Transfer Syntax to which to compress the DICOM image
imageWriter.dcmIIOFormatName:Image IO Writer Format Name|Image IO Writer Format Name
imageWriter.dcmJavaClassName:Java Class Name|Fully qualified Java class of Image IO Writer. If absent, use any Image Writer found for specified Format Name
imageWriter.dcmPatchJPEGLS:Patch JPEG-LS|Patch JPEG-LS after compressing
imageWriter.dcmPatchJPEGLS.JAI2ISO:Patch faulty JPEG-LS streams created by JAI-ImageIO CLibImageWriter, so the resulting JPEG-LS stream can be decoded by JPEG-LS compliant decoders
imageWriter.dcmPatchJPEGLS.JAI2ISO_IF_NO_APP_OR_COM:Amend JPEG-LS Coding parameters actually used by JAI-ImageIO, but only if the stream does NOT contain APPn or COM segments and is therefore more likely to have been actually created by JAI-ImageIO.
imageWriter.dcmPatchJPEGLS.ISO2JAI:Patch correct JPEG-LS streams, so they can be decompressed by the faulty JAI-ImageIOCLibImageReader. The resulting stream will still be correct JPEG-LS and can also be decoded by other decoders.
imageWriter.dcmPatchJPEGLS.ISO2JAI_IF_APP_OR_COM:Amend default JPEG-LS Coding parameters (for streams that do not contain them yet), but only if the stream contains APPn or COM segments - so it was certainly not created by JAI-ImageIO.
imageWriter.dcmImageWriteParam:Image Write Param|Image Write Parameter(s) (name=value) set at on Image Writer before compression
